Service definition for Prediction (v1.3).

Lets you access a cloud hosted machine learning service that makes it easy to build smart apps

For more information about this service, see the API Documentation

Sets the base path of the service on the server, for example "/prediction/v1.3". Must be URL-encoded. This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.

setPrettyPrint

public void setPrettyPrint(Boolean prettyPrint)
Sets the prettyPrint flag to server requests so that the response is formatted for readability. This makes debugging easier at the expense of slightly larger request sizes. The default is to use the server default, which is usually to pretty print.

getPrettyPrint

public Boolean getPrettyPrint()
Returns whether the request will be pretty printed, or null if no preference is set.
